1
00:00:04,605 --> 00:00:14,434
There is no restriction on the right time 
to chant or the wrong time to chant.

2
00:00:14,434 --> 00:00:18,208
You can take the Holy Name at any time.

3
00:00:18,208 --> 00:00:20,174
So Mahaprabhu Himself says that.

4
00:00:20,424 --> 00:00:23,161
[Transcendental Sound]

5
00:00:23,851 --> 00:00:28,652
And there is a famous instance with 
Gopāl Guru Goswāmī and ...

6
00:00:29,092 --> 00:00:31,432
I forget the other devotee’s name.

7
00:00:31,432 --> 00:00:39,579
But one thought that he shouldn’t take 
the Name when he was

8
00:00:39,579 --> 00:00:42,700
answering the calls of nature.

9
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:47,831
Because that is a polluted,
contaminated position.

10
00:00:47,831 --> 00:00:57,767
But from this Gopāl, who later became 
known as Gopāl Guru because here disciple

11
00:00:57,767 --> 00:01:01,793
took the position of guru by telling him, 
“Actually you can take the Holy Name

12
00:01:01,793 --> 00:01:06,543
under any circumstances, 
it would never be polluted

13
00:01:06,543 --> 00:01:10,516
by anything external”.

14
00:01:12,226 --> 00:01:22,452
But Śrīla Guru Maharāj will remind us,
“Is it Vaikuṇṭha-nāma-grahaṇam?”

15
00:01:22,452 --> 00:01:26,751
Is it sound that has Vaikuṇṭha quality,

16
00:01:26,751 --> 00:01:29,179
spiritual quality?

17
00:01:29,829 --> 00:01:34,217
This is the all-important factor.

18
00:01:34,217 --> 00:01:45,779
Just to parrot some particular sound, 
that’s not necessarily the Holy Name.

19
00:01:45,779 --> 00:01:49,676
So many times on this subject 
Śrīla Guru Maharāj would quote

20
00:01:49,696 --> 00:01:53,156
Jagadānanda Paṇḍit saying,

21
00:01:54,236 --> 00:01:59,055
nāmākṣara bahirāya baṭe, tabu nāma kabhu naya
[Pv: 7.1-3]

22
00:01:59,055 --> 00:02:05,684
That the nāmākṣara, means 
just the syllables of the Holy Name,

23
00:02:05,684 --> 00:02:09,577
the sounds, the objective sounds 
that we make,

24
00:02:09,577 --> 00:02:13,269
kabhu naya—that’s never 
the Holy Name.

25
00:02:13,269 --> 00:02:16,495
So there is something that’s
what it is in the objective world,

26
00:02:16,495 --> 00:02:21,353
and what it is in the subjective aspect.

27
00:02:21,353 --> 00:02:27,273
And the spiritual aspect of something
we trace to the subjective plane.

28
00:02:27,273 --> 00:02:30,249
So this Vaikuṇṭha-nāma-grahaṇam
of Guru Maharāj—

29
00:02:30,249 --> 00:02:32,363
does it have that Vaikuṇṭha quality,

30
00:02:32,363 --> 00:02:36,245
and here Vaikuṇṭha 
is synonymous with spiritual.

31
00:02:36,245 --> 00:02:41,375
This is from the Sixth Canto 
of the Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam

32
00:02:41,375 --> 00:02:47,389
in the Ajāmila section.

33
00:02:47,389 --> 00:02:55,992
So, quality, 
the quality of Kṛṣṇa-nām:

34
00:02:55,992 --> 00:03:00,507
sevonmukhe hi jihvādau
svayam eva sphuraty adaḥ

35
00:03:00,507 --> 00:03:02,707
ataḥ śrī-kṛṣṇa-nām ...
[Cc: Madhya, 17.136]

36
00:03:02,707 --> 00:03:06,807
Śrī-kṛṣṇa-nāmādi—
nāma, rūpa, guṇa, līlā—

37
00:03:06,807 --> 00:03:12,876
the Name, form, qualities, pastimes 
of Kṛṣṇa—grāhyam indriyaiḥ—

38
00:03:12,876 --> 00:03:17,975
they are beyond the grasp of the senses,
this is reinforcing what is said,

39
00:03:17,975 --> 00:03:23,787
it is not an objective experience, 
it is beyond the grasp of the senses,

40
00:03:23,787 --> 00:03:27,159
the mind and the intellect—

41
00:03:27,159 --> 00:03:28,830
The Holy Name proper.

42
00:03:28,830 --> 00:03:33,969
So that Holy Name can be taken 
under all circumstances.

